Its development and introduction were part of the naval aviation modernization efforts during the pre-World War II period.

Input.question1: What prayer is prayed on Yom Kippur?
Input.a1: Yom Kippur is the only day of the year when we pray Ne'ilah, the closing prayer, which is said as the sun is sinking in the west and this special day is coming to a close. Yizkor is also recited. Confession in Judaism is called Vidui (Hebrew וידוי ).
